  "prompt": "What are some good sources for free instrumental music to use in video tutorials?",
  "response": "Here are some excellent sources for free instrumental music that you can use in your video tutorials:\n\n1. **YouTube Audio Library**\n   - **Website**: [YouTube Audio Library](https://www.youtube.com/audiolibrary/music)\n   - **Description**: YouTube offers a vast collection of royalty-free music that you can use in your videos. The library includes a variety of genres, and you can filter by mood, genre, or instrument.\n\n2. **Free Music Archive (FMA)**\n   - **Website**: [Free Music Archive](https://freemusicarchive.org/)\n   - **Description**: FMA provides a curated selection of music from various artists. You can browse by genre, and many tracks are available under Creative Commons licenses, which often allow for free use in videos.\n\n3. **Incompetech**\n   - **Website**: [Incompetech](https://incompetech.com/music/royalty-free/)\n   - **Description**: Kevin MacLeod's Incompetech offers a wide range of instrumental music. While it's free to use, it's courteous to give credit to the composer in your video description.\n\n4. **Bensound**\n   - **Website**: [Bensound](https://www.bensound.com/)\n   - **Description**: Bensound offers high-quality royalty-free music. You can use the music for free if you credit Bensound and the composer in your video.\n\n5. **ccMixter**\n   - **Website**: [ccMixter](https://ccmixter.org/)\n   - **Description**: ccMixter is a community music site featuring remixes and original music under Creative Commons licenses. You can find a lot of instrumental tracks suitable for video tutorials.\n\n6. **Musopen**\n   - **Website**: [Musopen](https://musopen.org/music/)\n   - **Description**: Musopen offers a range of classical music that is free to use. It's a great resource if you're looking for instrumental tracks with a more classical feel.\n\n7. **Jamendo**\n   - **Website**: [Jamendo](https://www.jamendo.com/start)\n   - **Description**: Jamendo is a platform where independent artists share their music under Creative Commons licenses. You can search specifically for instrumental tracks.\n\nWhen using music from these sources, always check the specific licensing terms to ensure you're complying with any requirements, such as giving credit to the artist. This not only respects the creators' rights but also supports the community of musicians who offer their work for free.",
